<bug>
	<id>2912</id>
	<title>Run multiple instances simultaneously </title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">An use case for docker is to easily test clusters locally, deploying multiple instances of a certain application.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">I believe that adding a "-n &lt;number&gt;" option to run to start &lt;number&gt; instances would be helpful.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Example: sudo docker run -n 10 ubuntu /bin/echo hello world
Expected outcome: 10 instances of "ubuntu" start and execute the given command.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
